    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Friendly DiMaggio</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Leanard B Abrams letter protests allegations about Joe DiMaggio's supposed aloofness, citing his encounter with DiMaggio in the 1950's when seeking DiMaggio's autograph</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re an Oct. 26 letter about the supposed aloofness of Joe DiMaggio toward autograph-seekers:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re an Oct. 26 letter about the supposed aloofness of Joe DiMaggio toward autograph-seekers:</p>
        <p>Now wait a minute! It was in the late 50's and DiMaggio was leaving the old CBS building on East 52nd Street. I was entering the building. I asked him for his autograph. It was one on one, and he said, ''Sure.''  Then, I couldn't find a piece of paper, and I got flustered. Joe said, ''Take it easy.'' I found a matchbook in my pocket and Joe signed it. Enough about aloofness.</p>
        <p>LEONARD B. ABRAMS  Great Neck, N.Y., Oct. 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
